    "title": "Ilk (MGI:MGI:1195267)",
    "modelstate": "production",
    "deprecated": false,
    "date": "2024-07-25",
    "comment": "Michele Magrane (UniProt) challenged the annotation to the GO term \"protein serine/threonine kinase activity\" [GO:0004674] on 2024_07_24 with this comment: \"Recent evidence shows that ILK does not have protein kinase activity and is likely to act as a scaffold protein. See PMID:20005845 & PMID:21524996 which show lack of kinase activity as well as PMID:30367047 which describes a non-catalytic role for ILK and a recent review, PMID:35089438.\" \nFrom the review she listed, it seems that the actual function of ILK is still uncertain, so I deleted the kinase activity annotation without replacing it.",
